{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Notebook 02 — Rigid Registration (SimpleITK)\n",
    "\n",
    "Step-by-step interactive rigid registration:\n",
    "1. Load & preprocess volumes\n",
    "2. Visualize initial misalignment\n",
    "3. Run rigid registration (Euler3D, 6 DoF)\n",
    "4. Visualize result (slices, checkerboard, color overlay)\n",
    "5. Optional: affine refinement (12 DoF)\n",
    "6. Evaluate with Dice (if masks available)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import SimpleITK as sitk\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.io.loaders import load_volume, save_volume, sitk_to_numpy\n",
    "from src.preprocessing.preprocess import resample_to_spacing, normalize_intensity\n",
    "from src.registration.rigid import RigidRegistration, AffineRegistration, RegistrationConfig\n",
    "from src.visualization.visualize import (\n",
    "    plot_slices_comparison, plot_checkerboard, save_overlay, plot_metric_convergence\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 120"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load and preprocess"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "FIXED_PATH  = '../data/raw/fixed.nii.gz'\n",
    "MOVING_PATH = '../data/raw/moving.nii.gz'\n",
    "\n",
    "TARGET_SPACING = (1.0, 1.0, 1.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "fixed_raw  = load_volume(FIXED_PATH)\n",
    "moving_raw = load_volume(MOVING_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "fixed  = resample_to_spacing(fixed_raw, TARGET_SPACING)\n",
    "moving = resample_to_spacing(moving_raw, TARGET_SPACING)\n",
    "\n",
    "fixed_norm  = normalize_intensity(fixed, method='zscore')\n",
    "moving_norm = normalize_intensity(moving, method='zscore')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Visualize initial alignment"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Use the moving volume as a stand-in for 'registered before registration'\n",
    "fig = plot_slices_comparison(\n",
    "    fixed_norm, moving_norm, moving_norm,\n",
    "    titles=['Fixed', 'Moving', 'Moving (= before reg.)']\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Rigid registration\n",
    "\n",
    "Key hyperparameters:\n",
    "- **shrink_factors**: pyramid levels. `[4, 2, 1]` = 3 levels, starting at 1/4 resolution.\n",
    "- **smoothing_sigmas**: Gaussian pre-smoothing (mm) at each level.\n",
    "- **learning_rate**: optimizer step size. Reduce if not converging.\n",
    "- **sampling_percentage**: fraction of voxels sampled for MI. Increase for more accuracy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "config = RegistrationConfig(\n",
    "    metric='mattes_mi',\n",
    "    number_of_histogram_bins=50,\n",
    "    sampling_percentage=0.01,\n",
    "    learning_rate=1.0,\n",
    "    number_of_iterations=200,\n",
    "    shrink_factors=[4, 2, 1],\n",
    "    smoothing_sigmas=[2.0, 1.0, 0.0],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "rigid_reg = RigidRegistration(config)\n",
    "result = rigid_reg.register(fixed_norm, moving_norm, verbose=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nTransform parameters: {result.transform.GetParameters()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Apply transform and visualize"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "registered = result.apply(moving)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convergence\n",
    "plot_metric_convergence(result.metric_values, method_name='Rigid (Euler3D)')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Slices comparison\n",
    "plot_slices_comparison(fixed, moving, registered)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Checkerboard\n",
    "plot_checkerboard(fixed, registered)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Color overlay\n",
    "save_overlay(fixed, registered)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Affine refinement (optional)\n",
    "\n",
    "Warm-start affine from the rigid result to correct for residual scaling/shear."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "affine_reg = AffineRegistration(config)\n",
    "affine_result = affine_reg.register(\n",
    "    fixed_norm, moving_norm,\n",
    "    initial_transform=result.transform,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "registered_affine = affine_result.apply(moving)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_slices_comparison(\n",
    "    fixed, registered, registered_affine,\n",
    "    titles=['Fixed', 'After Rigid', 'After Affine']\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Save results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "save_volume(registered,        '../results/registered_rigid.nii.gz')\n",
    "save_volume(registered_affine, '../results/registered_affine.nii.gz')\n",
    "result.save_transform('../results/transform_rigid.tfm')\n",
    "affine_result.save_transform('../results/transform_affine.tfm')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Results saved to results/')"
   ]
  }
 ],
